                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F16 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F16</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At F16 measure voltage from circuit 12A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F16, 12A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 12 or 12A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (39). Turn ignition on and measure voltage from circuit 86 to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(39), 86 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 86, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (94) and measure voltage from (39) circuit 86 to (94) 86-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(39), 86 to (94) 86-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12&#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86-G, 62-G (without International elec.
                                engine), 11-GA or 11-GF to ground, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (39). With radio on measure voltage from (94) black wire of radio
                                pigtail to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(94), blk wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace radio.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F22 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F22</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install fuse F22 and measure voltage to ground at F22 and circuit 14D.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F22, 14D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 14D or 14R, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (39) and measure voltage from circuit 86E to gnd. This circuit
                                controls the radio station pre-sets.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(39), 86E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Power circuits OK, replace radio.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 86E, then repair. Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Was the right rear speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 13.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Was the left rear speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 17.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Was the right front speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 21.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Was the left front speaker functional prior to being disconnected for this test?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 24.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (57) and measure resistance across right rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across right rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (57) and disconnect conn. (58). Measure resistance across circuits
                                RIGHT (+) and RIGHT (-) going to speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(58) RIGHT (+) to RIGHT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit RIGHT (+) or RIGHT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (58) and disconnect conn. (16). Measure resistance across circuits
                                RIGHT (+) and RIGHT (-) going to speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(16), RIGHT (+) to RIGHT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit RIGHT (+) or RIGHT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (16) and disconnect conn. (94). Measure resistance across circuits
                                RIGHT (+) and RIGHT (-) going to speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(94), RIGHT (+) to RIGHT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit RIGHT (+) or RIGHT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (56) and measure resistance across left rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across left rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (56) and disconnect conn. (58). Measure resistance across circuits
                                LEFT (+) and LEFT (-) going to the speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(58) LEFT (+) to LEFT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit LEFT (+) or LEFT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (58) and disconnect conn. (16). At (16) measure resistance across
                                circuits LEFT (+) and LEFT (-) going to the speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(16) LEFT (+) to LEFT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit LEFT (+) or LEFT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (16) and disconnect conn. (94). Measure resistance across circuits
                                LEFT (+) and LEFT (-) going to the speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(94) LEFT (+) to LEFT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit LEFT (+) or LEFT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (260) and measure resistance across right front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across right front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (260) and disconnect conn. (159). Measure resistance across circuits
                                RTFNT(+) and RTFNT(-) going to the speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(159), RTFNT (+) to RTFNT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit RTFNT (+) or RTFNT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>23.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (159) and disconnect conn. (39). Measure resistance across circuits
                                RTFNT(+) and RTFNT(-) going to the speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(39), RTFNT (+) to RTFNT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit RTFNT (+) or RTFNT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>24.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (259) and measure resistance across left front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Across left front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 8 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace speaker assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>25.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (259) and disconnect conn. (159). Measure resistance across circuits
                                LTFNT (+), LTFNT (-) going to speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(159), LTFNT (+), LTFNT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit LTFNT (+) or LTFNT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (159). At conn. (39), measure resistance across circuits LTFNT (+) and
                                LTFNT (-) going to speaker.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(39), LTFNT (+) to LTFNT (-).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 9 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit LTFNT (+) or LTFNT (-), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Speaker circuits check good. Reconnect all circuits. If speaker(s) does not work,
                                replace radio.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
